\pard\f0\fs28 Perennials. Leaves flat or convolute; sheaths entire. Inflorescence a usually rather lax, often simple panicle. Spikelets slightly compressed laterally, with 1-several hermaphrodite florets and 2-3 sterile lemmas forming a terminal, clavate structure. Glumes more or less unequal, firmly membranous, 3- to 5-veined. Fertile lemma rounded on the back, coriaceous in fruit; veins 5-9(-13), sometimes obscure. Palea membranous, 2-keeled, 2-dentate. Lodicules 2, connate laterally.
