\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. M. nutans} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 66 (1753). Rhizomatous; stems 20-60 cm, slender, scabridulous near apex. Leaves 2-6 mm wide, flat, puberulent above; sheaths scabridulous, the lower purplish; ligule very short, truncate. Panicle 4-20 cm, lax, secund, simple or sparingly branched below. Spikelets 6-8 mm, eventually nodding, with 2-3 fertile florets, falling together when ripe. Glumes ovate to elliptical, obtuse, rounded on the back, persistent. Lemma of fertile florets elliptical to elliptic-oblong, obtuse, strongly veined, slightly longer than glumes, not shining. 2n = 18.{\i  Shady and often rocky places. Most of Europe, but rare in the Mediterranean region and the islands.} Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge He Hs Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W, K, E) Su Tu [Ho].
